# Model Pattern Guide

Models in this application follow a specific pattern as shown in [backend/app/Models/ClassesModel.php](mdc:backend/app/Models/ClassesModel.php).

## Model Structure
- Models extend a base model class
- Database table configuration is done in constructor
- Tables are defined in `DbTables` class
- Models use standard CRUD method names:
  - `getRecords()` - Fetch multiple records
  - `getRecord()` - Fetch single record
  - `createRecord()` - Insert new record
  - `updateRecord()` - Update existing record
  - `deleteRecord()` - Delete record

## Table Configuration
```php
public function __construct() {
    parent::__construct();
    $this->table = DbTables::$classesTable;
    foreach(DbTables::initTables() as $key) {
        if (property_exists($this, $key)) {
            $this->{$key} = DbTables::${$key};
        }
    }
}
```

## Best Practices
- Always use model methods for database operations
- Include proper where clauses for data isolation
- Use prepared statements for all queries
- Implement proper error handling
- Return standardized data structures
